What do you do when you have too many ripe bananas? Make banana bread of course. This vegan recipe is by my vegan friend @justj0nathan 
INGREDIENTS 
3-4 medium-sized overripe bananas mashed
1 1/2 cup white flour
1 teaspoon baking soda
1/2 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon cinnamon
1/2 cup of vegan margarine
1 cup white sugar
1/2 cup unsweetened apple sauce 
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 tablespoon white vinegar
1 cup chopped walnuts

DIRECTIONS
‚Ä¢Oil and lightly flour a standard cake pan.
‚Ä¢Preheat oven to 350¬∞F (175¬∞C). ‚Ä¢Combine flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon.
‚Ä¢In a separate bowl, cream together vegan margarine and sugar with a mixer. Add apple sauce, mashed bananas, and vanilla extract.
‚Ä¢Slowly combine the dry mixture to the wet. Using a rubber spatula, mix until just combined. Don't overmix, or you'll deflate the batter!
‚Ä¢Gently fold in the chopped walnuts along with the white vinegar. Again, only mix until combined. You will notice the batter begin to grow slightly and bubble. This is the baking soda reacting with the vinegar, and this will create a fluffy cake.
‚Ä¢Bake for about 50 minutes or until a toothpick poked in the centre comes out clean. #vegan #veganrecipes #bananabread #veganfood #veganism
